00:02:45.930 --> 00:02:50.930
{\an1}Episode 8
 A Small Wish

00:02:47.640 --> 00:02:50.310
Impressive horse girls seem to be
 appearing in ever-greater numbers.

00:02:50.310 --> 00:02:51.790
Never mind that...

00:02:51.790 --> 00:02:53.190
Ta-dah!

00:02:52.310 --> 00:02:56.000
Mejiro McQueen's <font color="#fff565">Third Win Looking Likely
</font><font color="#fbf4f3">Takes the Osaka Hai</font>

00:02:53.190 --> 00:02:56.000
This weekend is the Spring Tennoushou!

00:02:56.000 --> 00:02:58.890
And Rice is all fired up about 
taking you down, McQueen!

00:02:58.890 --> 00:03:00.460
Do your best!

00:03:00.460 --> 00:03:02.670
Rice has you in her crosshairs, huh?

00:03:02.670 --> 00:03:03.540
Yes.

00:03:03.540 --> 00:03:06.790
She's been following me around 
a fair bit lately, too.

00:03:06.790 --> 00:03:09.140
That goes to show she's in serious mode.

00:03:09.890 --> 00:03:13.100
All the better. It'll make 
the challenge worthwhile.

00:03:22.110 --> 00:03:25.280
The Spring Tennoushou is 3,200 meters long.

00:03:25.660 --> 00:03:31.400
I'm good at long distances, 
but McQueen-san has won it twice already,

00:03:31.400 --> 00:03:33.960
so she's got a clear experience advantage.

00:03:35.540 --> 00:03:36.950
McQueen-san...

00:03:56.730 --> 00:03:58.740
Rice hasn't been coming to school?!

00:03:58.740 --> 00:04:01.140
Not for the last two days, it seems.

00:04:01.140 --> 00:04:03.190
Do you suppose she's not 
going to be running?

00:04:03.190 --> 00:04:06.180
No way! There's hardly any time 
left before the Tennoushou!

00:04:06.180 --> 00:04:09.490
Maybe she's sick? Or she ate something funny?

00:04:09.490 --> 00:04:10.050
Like a spider.

00:04:10.050 --> 00:04:12.500
No one eats spiders!

00:04:12.500 --> 00:04:14.830
I wonder why she's missing, though.

00:04:26.260 --> 00:04:28.260
{\an8}Here

00:04:26.260 --> 00:04:28.260
Tracen
 Academy

00:04:26.260 --> 00:04:28.260
1-on-1

00:04:26.260 --> 00:04:28.260
1-on-1

00:04:40.470 --> 00:04:41.310
Rice...

00:04:42.820 --> 00:04:44.000
Bourbon-san...

00:04:59.390 --> 00:05:01.500
How did you find me?

00:05:01.730 --> 00:05:04.450
I spoke to the resident assistant,
 Hishi Amazon-san.

00:05:04.450 --> 00:05:07.930
I didn't think you would leave 
without telling someone.

00:05:07.930 --> 00:05:09.280
I see.

00:05:15.900 --> 00:05:17.120
Mental strength...

00:05:17.790 --> 00:05:21.200
I can't compare to McQueen-san in 
running ability or experience,

00:05:21.200 --> 00:05:23.920
so I need to have a stronger mindset.

00:05:23.920 --> 00:05:28.190
To do that, I decided to be alone, so I could
 face myself without any distractions.

00:05:29.530 --> 00:05:32.660
I think that the mind can 
help the body transcend.

00:05:34.000 --> 00:05:36.540
The mind can push the body past its limits!

00:05:37.470 --> 00:05:38.790
I agree.

00:05:39.140 --> 00:05:40.960
I'm going to get back to training.

00:05:41.380 --> 00:05:42.120
Right.

00:05:55.280 --> 00:05:58.560
Sweets! Sweets! Sweets!

00:05:55.940 --> 00:05:58.560
Rice still hasn't come back to school, huh?

00:05:58.560 --> 00:06:00.730
No. It's been three days now.

00:05:58.560 --> 00:06:05.030
Sweets! Sweets! Sweets!

00:06:00.730 --> 00:06:02.970
And Bourbon was missing too, today.

00:06:02.970 --> 00:06:06.890
Is it some kind of secret training,
 or has she given up?

00:06:05.030 --> 00:06:10.530
Sweets! Sweets! Sweets!

00:06:06.890 --> 00:06:10.530
I don't think so! I saw 
how motivated she looked.

00:06:14.450 --> 00:06:15.870
52.9!

00:06:15.870 --> 00:06:16.830
Wow!

00:06:16.830 --> 00:06:18.120
Looking good!

00:06:18.120 --> 00:06:20.820
Yes! I'm feeling more energetic and resilient

00:06:20.820 --> 00:06:23.680
than I did in the previous two Tennoushous.

00:06:23.680 --> 00:06:24.490
I see!

00:06:24.490 --> 00:06:26.630
I'd like to run the incline again, please.

00:06:26.630 --> 00:06:29.310
Whoa, isn't twice enough?

00:06:29.310 --> 00:06:31.010
Looking good and ready to go!

00:06:31.010 --> 00:06:33.510
McNice! McNice!

00:06:39.030 --> 00:06:43.020
More... More... More...

00:06:43.020 --> 00:06:43.980
More!

00:06:50.520 --> 00:06:52.450
Hey! What's up?

00:06:52.450 --> 00:06:54.970
No, it's nothing!

00:06:55.450 --> 00:06:57.390
What do you think's up with McQueen?

00:06:57.390 --> 00:06:58.510
No clue.

00:06:58.510 --> 00:07:01.700
But this attempt was even better 
than her last one.

00:07:01.700 --> 00:07:05.140
It's clear that McQueen is in
as good a shape as ever.

00:07:05.140 --> 00:07:07.280
Yeah, you're right.

00:07:16.920 --> 00:07:18.430
G-Good question.

00:07:18.430 --> 00:07:20.650
Their final tuning is going very well.

00:07:20.650 --> 00:07:22.650
There's no way Machi Tan could ever lose!

00:07:22.650 --> 00:07:25.060
She already beat Rice Shower once before!

00:07:25.060 --> 00:07:27.300
You do know she's beaten 
her more than once, right?

00:07:27.300 --> 00:07:28.760
What, for real?!

00:07:32.600 --> 00:07:35.520
'Kay, people, ask me anything about Palmer!

00:07:35.520 --> 00:07:38.950
As her certified bestie, I can tell you 
right now she's in GOAT condition!

00:07:38.950 --> 00:07:40.450
Palmer FTW!

00:07:44.110 --> 00:07:45.870
She's in really good shape.

00:07:45.870 --> 00:07:47.040
Yeah, it's impressive.

00:07:47.040 --> 00:07:49.510
I think we can count on 
McQueen's streak to continue.

00:07:49.510 --> 00:07:52.320
Can she become the first to win
three Spring Tennoushous in a row?

00:07:52.320 --> 00:07:55.160
I think so. In the condition 
she's in, she can handle it.

00:07:55.160 --> 00:07:56.380
Thank you!

00:07:56.380 --> 00:07:58.250
Any concerns about Rice Shower?

00:07:58.250 --> 00:08:00.390
She's apparently been absent 
from school for a few days.

00:08:00.390 --> 00:08:02.220
Not concerned at all.

00:08:02.220 --> 00:08:05.900
No matter who she's up against, 
McQueen is focused on her own running.

