You've got this!

00:09:21.430 --> 00:09:24.180
Mejiro McQueen

00:09:21.740 --> 00:09:22.770
How are you feeling?

00:09:22.770 --> 00:09:24.180
Perfect, I'd say.

00:09:24.180 --> 00:09:26.690
You nervous or anything?

00:09:27.550 --> 00:09:30.900
I do feel anxious about needing to win, yes.

00:09:30.900 --> 00:09:33.190
You've got a streak to protect, after all.

00:09:34.070 --> 00:09:37.130
I will run in a way that 
makes me fit to be your goal.

00:09:37.130 --> 00:09:38.410
Please, watch me.

00:09:38.410 --> 00:09:39.220
Okay.

00:09:39.220 --> 00:09:40.220
Good luck!

00:09:41.150 --> 00:09:44.290
Running past the stands now is Mejiro Palmer.

00:09:44.290 --> 00:09:46.390
She's expected to attempt to outrun 
the competition once again.

00:09:47.630 --> 00:09:49.290
Keep it hype, girl!

00:09:49.290 --> 00:09:53.360
She's been voted fourth most popular. 
What do you think that implies, Hosoe-san?

00:09:53.360 --> 00:09:56.370
In her last race, the 3,000-meter
 Hanshin Daishoten,

00:09:56.370 --> 00:09:58.850
she managed to secure a splendid 
victory via outrunning.

00:09:58.850 --> 00:10:00.480
We can expect to see
a great race from her.

00:10:00.480 --> 00:10:03.380
And here we have two other racers 
who are looking to win big.

00:10:03.380 --> 00:10:06.430
Ikuno Dictus and Machikane Tannhäuser 
seem to be in good spirits.

00:10:06.430 --> 00:10:07.620
Good luck, you two.

00:10:07.620 --> 00:10:09.690
Iku Dis! Machi Tan!

00:10:09.690 --> 00:10:11.760
Machikane Tannhäuser is third most popular,

00:10:11.760 --> 00:10:14.690
and has been gathering more and more 
attention from the fans lately.

00:10:14.690 --> 00:10:17.860
She's won her last two races, 
and has a lot of momentum.

00:10:17.860 --> 00:10:20.200
She's got a good chance at coming 
away with this spring's plaque.

00:10:20.200 --> 00:10:22.130
I bet she's got a
good race ahead of her.

00:10:22.130 --> 00:10:25.270
And number one with a 
bullet is Mejiro McQueen!

00:10:25.270 --> 00:10:29.210
I think it's fair to say that she's the 
horse girl closest to winning this race.

00:11:06.990 --> 00:11:11.000
Umamusume

00:11:06.990 --> 00:11:11.000
{\an2}Pretty Derby

00:11:11.760 --> 00:11:17.000
As the G1 Spring Tennoushou fanfare plays, 
the horse girls are now entering the gate.

00:11:17.000 --> 00:11:19.140
You can do this, McQueen!

00:11:19.140 --> 00:11:21.220
Please win for a third time!

00:11:21.220 --> 00:11:23.430
Don't sweat this streak stuff!

00:11:23.430 --> 00:11:25.280
That's kinda asking a lot.

00:11:25.280 --> 00:11:26.270
That's true.

00:11:26.270 --> 00:11:27.010
What's going on?

00:11:27.010 --> 00:11:28.070
Huh?

00:11:28.070 --> 00:11:29.550
What happened?

00:11:29.550 --> 00:11:30.640
Hey...

00:11:31.860 --> 00:11:33.020
She's not going in?

00:11:34.520 --> 00:11:37.020
What's going on?

00:11:40.540 --> 00:11:43.940
Oh, it looks like Mejiro McQueen 
hasn't entered the gate yet.

00:11:43.940 --> 00:11:45.530
That's odd.

00:11:45.530 --> 00:11:46.810
What the heck?

00:11:46.810 --> 00:11:48.920
What's wrong with McQueen-san?

00:11:48.920 --> 00:11:50.540
It's just like during her training.

00:11:50.540 --> 00:11:51.300
Seriously?

00:11:51.300 --> 00:11:52.820
What's gotten into her?

00:11:52.820 --> 00:11:54.290
McQueen...

00:11:56.090 --> 00:11:57.580
McQueen-san...

00:11:58.210 --> 00:12:00.770
What is she, a wild animal?

00:12:00.770 --> 00:12:04.060
It feels like she's ready to tear me apart.

00:12:04.840 --> 00:12:08.880
But I have my own reasons 
for winning this race.

00:12:09.310 --> 00:12:12.310
Mejiro McQueen is finally inside the gate.

00:12:12.310 --> 00:12:13.690
Okay, there she goes!

00:12:13.690 --> 00:12:15.310
Show them what you've got, McQueen!

00:12:15.550 --> 00:12:17.670
It takes power and stamina in equal measure

00:12:17.670 --> 00:12:20.450
to come out on top in this 3,200-meter 
trek around the Kyoto Racecourse.

00:12:20.940 --> 00:12:23.820
All 15 horse girls are now inside the gate.

00:12:23.820 --> 00:12:25.780
And now the Spring Tennoushou...

00:12:25.780 --> 00:12:26.680
has...

00:12:27.660 --> 00:12:29.280
begun!

00:12:29.280 --> 00:12:30.990
Go, McQueen!

00:12:30.190 --> 00:12:30.990
...san!

00:12:30.990 --> 00:12:33.290
Iku Dis! Machi Tan!

00:12:33.290 --> 00:12:34.720
McQueen!

00:12:34.720 --> 00:12:35.790
McQueen!

00:12:36.060 --> 00:12:38.790
Mejiro Palmer is in front, as expected.

00:12:39.160 --> 00:12:40.050
Got this!

00:12:40.050 --> 00:12:41.880
Time to outrun! Let's go!

00:12:41.880 --> 00:12:44.060
Further out from the 
center is Mejiro McQueen,

00:12:44.060 --> 00:12:46.290
who's sticking close behind Mejiro Palmer!

00:12:47.050 --> 00:12:48.550
Looking good, McQueen!

00:12:48.550 --> 00:12:49.500
No...

00:12:49.500 --> 00:12:50.450
What's wrong?

00:12:50.450 --> 00:12:52.310
They just started!

00:12:52.310 --> 00:12:54.500
She can't start chasing Palmer this soon.

00:12:54.500 --> 00:12:56.330
That's right, she can't!

00:12:56.330 --> 00:12:59.520
No... it's not Palmer she's worried about.

00:12:59.520 --> 00:13:00.900
I think it's...

00:13:00.900 --> 00:13:02.680
McQueen is currently in fourth place,

00:13:02.680 --> 00:13:06.150
and following her closely is Rice Shower, 
whose black hair is trailing behind her.

00:13:07.030 --> 00:13:09.570
Rice has been on McQueen the whole time.

00:13:09.570 --> 00:13:11.420
She's got her marked pretty clearly.

00:13:11.420 --> 00:13:13.540
But why not get behind her?

00:13:13.900 --> 00:13:18.040
Is she intentionally making her 
presence known to McQueen?

00:13:21.800 --> 00:13:22.870
McQueen!

00:13:22.870 --> 00:13:23.800
McQueen!

00:13:23.800 --> 00:13:24.910
McQueen...

00:13:24.910 --> 00:13:28.260
The way Rice-san has her marked so 
thoroughly reminds me of something.

00:13:28.510 --> 00:13:31.880
It's just like when Grass-chan was 
closing in during the Takarazuka Kinen.

00:13:31.880 --> 00:13:32.750
Really?

00:13:32.750 --> 00:13:34.890
I think I see the similarity.

00:13:34.890 --> 00:13:35.790
Grass-chan?!

00:13:35.790 --> 00:13:36.810
Hello there.

00:13:36.810 --> 00:13:39.240
How is Rice-chan like you, though?

00:13:39.240 --> 00:13:41.020
I can't say for sure.

00:13:41.020 --> 00:13:44.710
But it does feel something like fate.

00:13:48.100 --> 00:13:52.370
The 15 horse girls are bathed in cheers 
as they cross in front of the stands!

00:13:52.370 --> 00:13:54.060
Settle down, McQueen!

00:13:54.060 --> 00:13:55.520
Don't worry about anyone else!

00:13:55.520 --> 00:13:56.830
Stick to your own pace!

00:13:57.040 --> 00:13:58.500
He's right.

00:13:58.500 --> 00:14:02.590
I was able to defeat Teio last time 
because I focused on my own running.

00:14:02.590 --> 00:14:03.600
But...

00:14:05.340 --> 00:14:08.360
This pace... isn't suited 
to a 3,200-meter race!

00:14:08.360 --> 00:14:11.920
I need to let my legs stay cool, so that 
I'll have enough to rush to the front!

00:14:12.680 --> 00:14:13.690
Go!

00:14:13.690 --> 00:14:14.690
2:04?

00:14:14.690 --> 00:14:15.730
Whoa, isn't that...

00:14:15.730 --> 00:14:19.800
That's two seconds faster to reach the 
2,000-meter mark than the last Tennoushou!

00:14:20.340 --> 00:14:22.010
Is she gonna be okay with that kind of pace?!

00:14:22.010 --> 00:14:23.650
Of course she is.

00:14:23.910 --> 00:14:25.670
I have faith.

00:14:25.670 --> 00:14:27.470
McQueen's gonna be okay!

00:14:28.050 --> 00:14:29.700
Mejiro Palmer is in first place.

00:14:29.700 --> 00:14:30.780
She's got a lead of five lengths.

00:14:31.070 --> 00:14:33.540
They're now entering the 
incline on the third corner.

00:14:33.540 --> 00:14:35.810
More! I need to run even more!

00:14:36.150 --> 00:14:38.520
As they reach the third corner's incline,

00:14:38.520 --> 00:14:40.790
they'll really begin to feel the 
Spring Tennoushou's stamina drain!

00:14:43.330 --> 00:14:45.630
Whoa, and Mejiro McQueen is 
moving up on the outside!

00:14:45.630 --> 00:14:46.800
She's entered her spurt!

00:14:46.800 --> 00:14:47.630
Here she comes!

00:14:47.630 --> 00:14:50.300
She's closing in on Mejiro Palmer!

00:14:50.300 --> 00:14:51.840
It's Palmer and McQueen!

00:14:51.840 --> 00:14:54.120
But further out, it's Rice Shower!

00:14:54.120 --> 00:14:56.180
Rice Shower is moving up, too!

00:14:56.180 --> 00:14:57.750
She's not losing her at all!

00:14:57.750 --> 00:14:59.830
Is something going on with McQueen-san?

00:14:59.830 --> 00:15:02.520
No, it's not McQueen.

00:15:02.890 --> 00:15:05.760
Something's going on with her opponent.

00:15:06.780 --> 00:15:08.250
Go! McQueen!

00:15:08.250 --> 00:15:09.830
McQueen!

00:15:08.750 --> 00:15:09.640
Rice...

00:15:10.320 --> 00:15:14.070
I want to run with you, too, Bourbon-san.

00:15:15.150 --> 00:15:16.940
Go, Rice.

00:15:20.270 --> 00:15:21.950
Coming around the fourth corner,

00:15:21.950 --> 00:15:23.640
the trio will face off down the final stretch.

00:15:23.640 --> 00:15:24.960
Tannhäuser has joined them.

00:15:24.960 --> 00:15:27.080
But who will seize the lead?

00:15:29.250 --> 00:15:32.050
It's Mejiro McQueen! Mejiro McQueen is in first!

00:15:32.050 --> 00:15:33.260
Wait...

00:15:33.600 --> 00:15:36.010
On the outside! On the outside!

00:15:36.010 --> 00:15:39.820
It's Rice Shower! Rice Shower is closing in!

00:15:39.820 --> 00:15:41.020
Look at her go!

00:15:41.710 --> 00:15:44.480
This pressure... but I'm not through yet!

00:15:46.710 --> 00:15:49.510
Rice Shower has now caught up!

00:15:50.570 --> 00:15:52.360
Don't lose, McQueen!

00:15:52.360 --> 00:15:54.400
This is McQueen's attempt 
at a third championship,

00:15:54.400 --> 00:15:58.410
but will we see Rice Shower 
thwart another accomplishment?!

00:15:58.410 --> 00:16:00.190
Oh, come on, don't do this!

00:16:00.190 --> 00:16:01.340
McQueen, you can do it!

00:16:01.340 --> 00:16:04.170
Rice Shower! Are you trying 
to play the heel again?!

00:16:05.570 --> 00:16:06.670
I'm...

00:16:08.990 --> 00:16:10.710
not a heel.

00:16:21.770 --> 00:16:23.180
I'm a hero!

00:16:29.610 --> 00:16:32.240
Rice Shower passes her! 
Rice Shower passes her!

00:16:32.240 --> 00:16:34.230
It's Rice Shower! She's in first!

00:16:34.230 --> 00:16:37.870
The same Rice Shower who upset 
Mihono Bourbon at the Kikkashou!

00:16:38.080 --> 00:16:39.870
Rice Shower has taken the lead!

00:16:40.110 --> 00:16:42.610
That lead grows from two lengths to three!

00:16:42.610 --> 00:16:46.580
And Rice Shower crosses 
the goal in first place!

00:16:49.500 --> 00:16:50.890
McQueen...

00:16:52.200 --> 00:16:53.470
Look at that time!

00:16:53.470 --> 00:16:54.970
Record

00:16:59.880 --> 00:17:01.340
That's a new record.

00:17:02.540 --> 00:17:04.230
McQueen-san...

00:17:04.230 --> 00:17:06.940
I knew that she was strong, 
but I had no idea.

00:17:06.940 --> 00:17:08.730
I'm gonna take Rice down.

00:17:09.630 --> 00:17:10.980
Impressive.

00:17:14.240 --> 00:17:16.990
Record

00:17:14.930 --> 00:17:16.270
A record!

00:17:26.910 --> 00:17:28.220
I lost.

00:17:30.720 --> 00:17:32.130
What the hell?

00:17:32.960 --> 00:17:34.430
She did it again!

00:17:34.430 --> 00:17:37.150
I was really looking forward 
to McQueen's third win.

00:17:37.150 --> 00:17:38.160
Why's this keep happening?!

00:17:38.160 --> 00:17:38.840
Unbelievable!

00:17:39.740 --> 00:17:40.970
What a disappointment.

00:17:44.240 --> 00:17:45.860
I shouldn't have bothered coming.

00:17:50.380 --> 00:17:51.910
This is so lame.

00:18:45.610 --> 00:18:46.560
Rice...

00:18:55.570 --> 00:18:57.770
Congratulations on your win, Rice.

00:19:01.570 --> 00:19:02.500
I...

00:19:03.670 --> 00:19:06.520
ruined a lot of people's dreams again.

00:19:07.350 --> 00:19:09.540
That's what it means to win.

00:19:09.540 --> 00:19:11.190
It's a competition, after all.

00:19:11.890 --> 00:19:16.100
If someone wins, someone else will 
be hurt, and have their dream end.

00:19:16.590 --> 00:19:18.230
That's just how it is.

00:19:19.090 --> 00:19:21.290
Booing still hurts to hear, though.

00:19:21.900 --> 00:19:24.660
It really does.

00:19:24.990 --> 00:19:27.840
Being booed is an honor when 
you're the challenger.

00:19:27.840 --> 00:19:29.900
You don't need to feel bad about it.

00:19:30.630 --> 00:19:35.690
But, one day, I'm sure it'll turn into 
cheers and words of encouragement.

00:19:36.550 --> 00:19:39.440
If you keep winning, I'm sure that will happen.

00:19:40.990 --> 00:19:44.870
After all, your name is Rice Shower.

00:19:48.820 --> 00:19:49.620
Yeah!

00:19:50.600 --> 00:19:53.300
I'll do my best, okay?

00:19:54.260 --> 00:19:57.550
I'd expect nothing less from my hero.

00:19:59.400 --> 00:20:00.690
McQueen!
Congratulations on your <font face="Comic Sans MS">second place </font><font face="Trebuchet MS">win!</font>

00:20:00.690 --> 00:20:02.030
What a feast!

00:20:02.030 --> 00:20:03.530
It certainly is.

00:20:03.780 --> 00:20:05.870
Spe-senpai! Time out for now!

00:20:05.870 --> 00:20:08.460
Huh? Where's McQueen?

00:20:08.460 --> 00:20:12.460
Good point. It didn't end up being 
a celebration, but we still need our star.

00:20:12.830 --> 00:20:15.010
Could you go find her, Teio?

00:20:15.010 --> 00:20:16.420
Yeah, sure.

00:20:16.420 --> 00:20:17.420
Hey.

00:20:19.320 --> 00:20:20.220
Take these.

00:20:35.640 --> 00:20:38.850
McQueen, you ran a fine race.

00:20:38.850 --> 00:20:41.150
Yes, likewise.

00:20:41.530 --> 00:20:43.990
It's a shame your streak was broken.

00:20:43.990 --> 00:20:45.990
You're bringing that up, too?

00:20:46.950 --> 00:20:49.910
Everyone on my team has 
been so considerate.

00:20:49.910 --> 00:20:52.840
And I'd be lying if I said it didn't bother me,

00:20:52.840 --> 00:20:54.980
but I'm not really that upset.

00:20:55.560 --> 00:20:59.180
Really? You seemed a bit lonely.

00:21:02.560 --> 00:21:04.530
I do feel a bit guilty.

00:21:04.530 --> 00:21:05.860
Guilty?

00:21:05.860 --> 00:21:09.220
Yes. For disappointing the fans who were 
cheering me on, of course,

00:21:09.220 --> 00:21:10.880
but for disappointing Tokai Teio in particular.

00:21:11.830 --> 00:21:15.200
Teio is working hard to 
complete her rehabilitation.

00:21:15.800 --> 00:21:21.100
With her goal being to race against me,
 an unbeatable horse girl.

00:21:21.480 --> 00:21:25.590
And yet, my performance 
was less than adequate.

00:21:28.900 --> 00:21:31.990
I will run in a way that 
makes me fit to be your goal.

00:21:33.150 --> 00:21:34.380
McQueen...

00:21:37.500 --> 00:21:40.220
Overconfidence in my knack 
for handling the race's distance...

00:21:40.220 --> 00:21:42.360
A false sense of security,
due to it being my third time...

00:21:42.360 --> 00:21:45.400
And most of all, the fact
that I was arrogant enough

00:21:45.400 --> 00:21:46.960
to think I was racing for Teio's sake...

00:21:46.960 --> 00:21:48.670
It's no wonder I lost.

00:21:49.940 --> 00:21:55.720
I was simply less focused 
on victory than Rice Shower.

00:21:56.910 --> 00:21:59.900
But I won't make the same mistake again.

00:21:59.900 --> 00:22:03.380
I need to maintain 
my position as the strongest.

00:22:04.000 --> 00:22:07.670
At the Takarazuka Kinen, I will win.

00:22:07.670 --> 00:22:09.030
McQueen...

00:22:09.030 --> 00:22:13.740
My rotation has me running in the Yasuda Kinen,
 and then the Takarazuka Kinen.

00:22:14.120 --> 00:22:18.620
We'll be racing. And I don't 
intend to let you win.

00:22:19.300 --> 00:22:22.010
I'm truly blessed.

00:22:22.010 --> 00:22:24.970
I have so many rivals...

00:22:32.770 --> 00:22:34.260
The Takarazuka Kinen!

00:22:35.305 --> 00:23:35.226
